Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of reaching consensus in grouping problems such as clustering, community detection in networks, and multiple parametric model estimation. This falls under the broad area of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the computational Gestalt program, which is related to computer vision and image processing, and could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the proposed biclustering algorithm involves optimization and could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
